text.section:
A person may not dispense a prescription drug by filling or refilling a written or oral prescription of an authorized provider unless the drug bears a label that, in addition to any requirements of the Department or federal law, contains:
the name and address of the dispenser;
the serial number and date of the prescription;
the name of the authorized provider; and
if stated in the prescription, the name and address of the patient and the directions for use.

Except as otherwise provided under this title, a person may not:
manufacture, distribute, or possess with intent to distribute a prescription drug;
affix a false or counterfeit label to a package, container, or other receptacle containing a prescription drug;
omit, remove, alter, or obliterate a label or symbol that is required by federal, State, or local law on a prescription drug; or
obtain or attempt to obtain a prescription drug by:
fraud, deceit, or misrepresentation;
the counterfeiting or altering of a prescription or written order;
concealing a material fact;
using a false name or address;
falsely assuming the title of or falsely representing that the person is a manufacturer, distributor, or authorized provider; or
making or issuing a false or counterfeit prescription or written order.
